INSERT INTO `wp_evf_entrymeta` VALUES (1,1,'website_url_9492','https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2019/10/20/14/49/animal-4563886_960_720.jpg'),(2,1,'paragraph_text_9667','Red Breasted'),(3,1,'dropdown_3916','Birds'),(4,1,'single_line_text_5188','Robin'),(5,1,'paragraph_text_9357','________'),(6,2,'website_url_9492','https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2019/10/20/14/49/animal-4563886_960_720.jpg'),(7,2,'single_line_text_5188','Robin'),(8,2,'paragraph_text_9667','Red Breasted'),(9,2,'dropdown_3916','Birds'),(10,2,'paragraph_text_9357','________'),(11,3,'website_url_9492','https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2019/10/20/14/49/animal-4563886_960_720.jpg'),(12,3,'single_line_text_5188','Robin'),(13,3,'dropdown_3916','Birds'),(14,4,'website_url_9492','https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2019/10/20/14/49/animal-4563886_960_720.jpg'),(15,4,'single_line_text_5188','Robin'),(16,4,'dropdown_3916','Birds'),(17,5,'website_url_9492','https://www.montwt.co.uk/sites/default/files/styles/node_hero_lap/public/2017-12/CommonLizardjonhawkinsSurreyHillsPhotography.jpg?h=3561ba34&itok=0dGS5AYS'),(18,5,'single_line_text_5188','Common Lizard'),(19,5,'dropdown_3916','Reptiles'),(20,6,'website_url_9492','https://c.pxhere.com/images/bf/5c/d3a8d6001bee62900a0b2d22d1ec-1601628.jpg!d'),(21,6,'single_line_text_5188','Marsh Violets'),(22,6,'paragraph_text_9667','As its name suggests, the Marsh violet likes damp spots, such as marshes, bogs and wet woods. It is a low-growing plant with kidney-shaped leaves and pale lilac flowers.'),(23,6,'dropdown_3916','Plants'),(24,6,'multiple_choice_1037','a:3:{s:4:\"name\";s:115:\"Please check if you would like an individual page creating for this entry?  If yes, fill in Full Description below:\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"radio\";s:5:\"label\";s:2:\"No\";}'),(25,7,'website_url_9492','https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2016/03/22/01/02/common-toad-1272014_960_720.jpg'),(26,7,'single_line_text_5188','Common Toad'),(27,7,'paragraph_text_9667','Despite its warts and ancient associations with witches, the common toad is a gardener\'s friend, sucking up slugs and snails. It is famous for migrating en masse to its breeding ponds.'),(28,7,'dropdown_3916','Amphibians'),(29,7,'multiple_choice_1037','a:3:{s:4:\"name\";s:115:\"Please check if you would like an individual page creating for this entry?  If yes, fill in Full Description below:\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"radio\";s:5:\"label\";s:3:\"Yes\";}'),(30,7,'paragraph_text_9357','Common toads are amphibians, breeding in ponds during the spring and spending much of the rest of the year feeding in woodland, gardens, hedgerows and tussocky grassland. They are famous for their mass migrations back to their breeding ponds on the first warm, damp evenings of the year, often around St. Valentine\'s Day.\r\nCommon toads tend to breed in larger, deeper ponds than common frogs, but still frequent gardens. They hibernate over winter, often under log piles, stones or even in old flower pots!'),(31,8,'single_line_text_5188','Barn Owl'),(32,8,'paragraph_text_9667','With heart-shaped face, buff back and wings and pure white underparts, the barn owl is a distinctive and much-loved countryside bird.'),(33,8,'dropdown_3916','Birds'),(34,8,'multiple_choice_1037','a:3:{s:4:\"name\";s:115:\"Please check if you would like an individual page creating for this entry?  If yes, fill in Full Description below:\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"radio\";s:5:\"label\";s:2:\"No\";}'),(35,9,'single_line_text_5188','Beaver'),(36,9,'paragraph_text_9667','A water and on land creature'),(37,9,'dropdown_3916','Mammals'),(38,9,'multiple_choice_1037','a:3:{s:4:\"name\";s:115:\"Please check if you would like an individual page creating for this entry?  If yes, fill in Full Description below:\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"radio\";s:5:\"label\";s:2:\"No\";}'),(39,10,'website_url_9492','https://www.montwt.co.uk/sites/default/files/styles/grid_teaser/public/2018-05/MaleAdonisBlueColinWilliams01062014.JPG?h=e982d60e&itok=_E62St6V'),(40,10,'single_line_text_5188','Adonis blue'),(41,10,'paragraph_text_9667','The rare Adonis blue can be spotted on sunny chalk grasslands throughout summer. Males are a dazzling sky-blue in colour, while females are duller brown.'),(42,10,'dropdown_3916','Invertebrates'),(43,10,'multiple_choice_1037','a:3:{s:4:\"name\";s:115:\"Please check if you would like an individual page creating for this entry?  If yes, fill in Full Description below:\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"radio\";s:5:\"label\";s:2:\"No\";}'),(44,11,'single_line_text_4211','Roundton Hill'),(45,11,'paragraph_text_9583','Views from the top of Roundton can be spectacular at any time of year, but to catch the ‘spring ephemerals’ you need to get there early – March/April. Throughout the Spring and Summer, bird song fills the air; also keep your eyes peeled for butterflies, making use of the varied habitats.'),(46,11,'website_url_7319','https://www.montwt.co.uk/nature-reserves/roundton-hill'),(47,12,'single_line_text_1259','Metals'),(48,12,'paragraph_text_8070','Various metals will form a key feature in the new Dyfi Wildlife Centre.\r\nWhy?\r\nFor centuries the hills and mountains around the Dyfi River have been the focus of rampant mining activity. It has all come to an end now, but the landscape our ancestors left behind still bear the hallmarks of their metallurgic activities. Romans mined copper on the north side of the Dyfi and Charles I found great success with silver on the south side, so much so, he moved the Royal Mint from London to Aberystwyth Castle in the 1640s and then even nearer to Cors Dyfi in 1649 – the little village of Furnace.'),(49,12,'website_url_7380','http://www.dyfiospreyproject.com/sites/default/files/images/53233386_2384334588461368_3065223863148216320_o.jpg'),(50,13,'first_name_3641','Clarach'),(51,13,'single_line_text_9436','Rutland'),(52,14,'first_name_4789','Ysabel'),(53,14,'single_line_text_1212','Delete wildlife ID 2'),(54,14,'paragraph_text_1823','This animal has not been sighted in a while therefore we would like to remove this from the map.'),(55,15,'website_url_9492','https://www.montwt.co.uk/sites/default/files/styles/grid_teaser/public/2018-01/ChubcJackPerks.jpg?h=52409af7&itok=wsPNlBy2'),(56,15,'single_line_text_5188','Chub'),(57,15,'paragraph_text_9667','The silvery chub can be seen gathering in large shoals in lowland rivers and streams. It is a member of the carp family and looks very similar to the dace, but is larger and has redder fins. A freshwater fish'),(58,15,'dropdown_3916','Fish'),(59,15,'multiple_choice_1037','a:3:{s:4:\"name\";s:115:\"Please check if you would like an individual page creating for this entry?  If yes, fill in Full Description below:\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"radio\";s:5:\"label\";s:2:\"No\";}'),(60,16,'website_url_9492','https://www.montwt.co.uk/sites/default/files/styles/grid_teaser/public/2018-01/MHA_08_020711_1097.jpg?h=59f9d53c&itok=5x2aACtb'),(61,16,'single_line_text_5188','Sphagnum Moss'),(62,16,'paragraph_text_9667','Sphagnum Mosses carpet the ground with colour on our marshes, heaths and moors. They play a vital role in the creation of peat bogs: by storing water in their spongy forms, they prevent the decay of dead plant material and eventually form peat.'),(63,16,'dropdown_3916','Other'),(64,16,'multiple_choice_1037','a:3:{s:4:\"name\";s:115:\"Please check if you would like an individual page creating for this entry?  If yes, fill in Full Description below:\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"radio\";s:5:\"label\";s:3:\"Yes\";}'),(65,16,'paragraph_text_9357','Sphagnum Mosses carpet the ground with colour on our marshes, heaths and moors. They play a vital role in the creation of peat bogs: by storing water in their spongy forms, they prevent the decay of dead plant material and eventually form peat.\r\nThere are at least ten species of Sphagnum Moss in the UK, which are very difficult to tell apart. These species range in colour from red and pink, to orange and green. Sphagnum Moss plants are very small, but they grow closely together, forming spongy carpets; \'hummocks\' are even created when the mosses grow to form large mounds up to a metre high.'),(66,17,'website_url_9492','https://thenypost.files.wordpress.com/2018/07/drunk-seaguls-england.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&w=915'),(67,17,'single_line_text_5188','Seagulls'),(68,17,'paragraph_text_9667','Gulls or seagulls are seabirds of the family Laridae in the suborder Lari. They are most closely related to the terns (family Sternidae) and only distantly related to auks, skimmers, and more distantly to the waders.'),(69,17,'dropdown_3916','Birds'),(70,17,'multiple_choice_1037','a:3:{s:4:\"name\";s:115:\"Please check if you would like an individual page creating for this entry?  If yes, fill in Full Description below:\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"radio\";s:5:\"label\";s:2:\"No\";}'),(71,18,'first_name_3641','Pearl'),(72,18,'single_line_text_9436','London');
